450
00:31:57.240 --> 00:32:04.240
You know, there's nothing in the New Testament, by the way, that prescribes us having like tangible objects like around our house or whatever.

451
00:32:04.240 --> 00:32:06.240
But it doesn't forbid it either.

452
00:32:06.240 --> 00:32:13.240
So I think it's, you know, it is a good practice to have little reminders here and there that says, you know, this is where the Lord provided for us.

453
00:32:13.240 --> 00:32:18.240
Certainly we see that pattern throughout the Old Testament, these reminders along the way of the Lord's goodness.

454
00:32:18.240 --> 00:32:24.240
Maybe it's a prayer journal for you where you jot down where the answers of prayer have come.

455
00:32:24.240 --> 00:32:35.240
The important thing is that we remember how the Lord is provided so that we might retell them for generations to come that they too might know and trust in the Lord.

456
00:32:36.240 --> 00:32:45.240
But you know, when you come to the New Testament, the Lord has given us a tangible reminder of the greatest thing he has provided for us.

457
00:32:45.240 --> 00:32:46.240
Hasn't he?

458
00:32:46.240 --> 00:32:51.240
He's given us this reminder of the bread of life.

459
00:32:51.240 --> 00:32:56.240
The greatest gift, which is the Lord Jesus who gave his life.

460
00:32:56.240 --> 00:32:58.240
And he died so that we might live.

461
00:32:58.240 --> 00:33:01.240
Let's hear these words from 1 Corinthians 11.

462
00:33:01.240 --> 00:33:05.240
It says, the Lord Jesus on the night when he was betrayed took bread.

463
00:33:05.240 --> 00:33:12.240
When he had given thanks, he broke it and said, this is my body, which is for you.

464
00:33:12.240 --> 00:33:16.240
Do this in remembrance of me.

465
00:33:20.240 --> 00:33:23.240
In the same way, he took the cup.

466
00:33:23.240 --> 00:33:29.240
After supper saying, this cup is the new covenant in my blood.

467
00:33:29.240 --> 00:33:35.240
Do this as often as you drink it in remembrance of me.

468
00:33:35.240 --> 00:33:43.240
For as often as you eat this bread and drink this cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until he comes.

469
00:33:44.240 --> 00:33:48.240
So Jesus died that we might live.

470
00:33:48.240 --> 00:33:51.240
He is the one who satisfies the longing of our souls.

471
00:33:51.240 --> 00:33:59.240
When we partake in this bread and wine by faith, we remember and proclaim his death until he comes.

472
00:33:59.240 --> 00:34:04.240
And this is a reminder wherever we end up in the coming months and years.

473
00:34:04.240 --> 00:34:06.240
It's a reminder we'll take with us.

474
00:34:06.240 --> 00:34:10.240
We've got the bread and the wine to remind us of the true bread of life.

475
00:34:10.240 --> 00:34:13.240
So I'd like for you to invite us to come to the Lord's table.

476
00:34:13.240 --> 00:34:17.240
That we might taste and see that the Lord is good.

477
00:34:17.240 --> 00:34:21.240
So let's pray together before we come.

478
00:34:21.240 --> 00:34:50.240
Lord, all too often we are a people who, instead of looking at your abundant grace that you've shown us in Jesus,

479
00:34:50.240 --> 00:34:56.240
focus on ourselves, focus on our problems, we grumble and complain.

480
00:34:56.240 --> 00:35:00.240
And all the while, Lord, you are reigning.

481
00:35:00.240 --> 00:35:04.240
You're working all things together for our good.

482
00:35:04.240 --> 00:35:09.240
Lord, we thank you that you look upon people like us, sinful people,

483
00:35:09.240 --> 00:35:14.240
and you pour out your grace upon us in Jesus.

484
00:35:14.240 --> 00:35:18.240
Lord, I pray that you would humble us even now.

485
00:35:18.240 --> 00:35:22.240
And Lord, that you would show us the sufficiency of your grace.

486
00:35:22.240 --> 00:35:27.240
And Lord, we thank you that Jesus took all of our sin upon himself.

487
00:35:27.240 --> 00:35:31.240
Lord, he died in our place.

488
00:35:31.240 --> 00:35:34.240
And Lord, we thank you that we can receive him by faith,

489
00:35:34.240 --> 00:35:39.240
knowing that in him you graciously receive us to yourself.

490
00:35:39.240 --> 00:35:45.240
So Lord, as we come to your table this morning, help us to be looking to Jesus by faith.

491
00:35:45.240 --> 00:35:49.240
Lord, as we receive this bread and receive this cup,

492
00:35:49.240 --> 00:35:56.240
I pray that in our hearts we would taste and see, Lord, that you truly are good.

493
00:35:56.240 --> 00:35:59.240
I pray this in Jesus' name. Amen.

